  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Envoy today has support for dynamically resolving the host from the HTTP authority header using the dynamic forward proxy filter (https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/intro/arch_overview/http/http_proxy). This is very useful when we have to capture and forward arbitrary HTTP traffic under a domain (like `*.google.com`) to an external envoy gateway that in turn forwards to the right destination.\r\n\r\nWe need a similar mechanism for TLS traffic as well, i.e. dynamically resolve the upstream based on the incoming SNI value and forward. With this support, we can capture all TLS traffic for a set of hosts (e.g., `*.googleapis.com`) and route them through a blessed egress gateway where we can do sni passthrough on the listener side, but dynamic resolution based on the sni on the upstream.\r\n\r\ncc @lizan ",
